  {
    "id": "present-continuous",
    "title": "Present Continuous Tense (-yor)",
    "description": "Learn to express actions happening right now",
    "difficulty": "beginner",
    "sections": [
      {
        "type": "explanation",
        "content": "The present continuous tense is formed by adding -yor to the verb stem, followed by personal suffixes. The vowel before -yor follows 4-way harmony (ı/i/u/ü)."
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": "Conjugation of 'gelmek' (to come)",
        "table": {
          "headers": ["Pronoun", "Turkish", "English"],
          "rows": [
            ["Ben", "geliyorum", "I am coming"],
            ["Sen", "geliyorsun", "You are coming"],
            ["O", "geliyor", "He/she is coming"],
            ["Biz", "geliyoruz", "We are coming"],
            ["Siz", "geliyorsunuz", "You (pl) are coming"],
            ["Onlar", "geliyorlar", "They are coming"]
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "explanation",
        "content": "If the verb stem ends in a vowel, drop it before adding -yor. Example: bekle-mek → bekl-iyor (is waiting)."
      }
    ],
    "exercises": [
      {
        "type": "conjugation",
